Key Match Events: France defeated Belgium 2-0 with goals from Kolo in the 29th minute and Dembele in the 57th minute.
Kone and Digne received yellow cards for France in the 4th and 8th minutes respectively.
Openda and Tielemans received yellow cards for Belgium in the 8th and 38th minutes respectively.
Pre-Game Insights: Belgium aimed for back-to-back wins in the UEFA Nations League.
Belgium's head coach Domenico Tedesco named a side without Thibaut Courtois and Romelu Lukaku.
Kevin De Bruyne and Jeremy Doku were expected to support the central striker for Belgium.
Lois Openda was expected to start as the central striker for Belgium.
Maxim De Cuyper was expected to start at left-back for Belgium.
